  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Clinic Nurse",
  "description": "<p>We are a dynamic and growing boutique medical group seeking a skilled, compassionate, and dedicated <strong>Clinic Nurse</strong> to join our medical team. The successful candidate will play a key role in delivering high-quality patient care and supporting doctors in providing excellent medical services.</p><h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Provide comprehensive patient care and education, including taking vital signs, administering and dispensing medications, and performing nursing procedures as directed by the doctors</p></li><li><p>Assist doctors during patient consultations, examinations, and minor procedures</p></li><li><p>Accurately document patient care activities and maintain up-to-date medical records in the electronic medical record (EMR) system</p></li><li><p>Coordinate patient care with doctors, nurses, and other healthcare support staff to ensure continuity of care</p></li><li><p>Adhere strictly to infection control protocols and maintain a clean, safe, and well-organised clinical environment</p></li><li><p>Support reception and administrative duties, as well as other nursing-related tasks, as required</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Registered Nurse (RN) with a valid practising licence in Singapore</p></li><li><p>Minimum of <strong>3 years’ clinical experience</strong>, preferably in primary care or family medicine</p></li><li><p>Strong communication and interpersonal skills with a patient-centric approach</p></li><li><p>Proficient in using electronic medical record systems</p></li><li><p>Ability to work independently as well as collaboratively within a multidisciplinary team</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Education</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Diploma (Associate Degree) or Bachelor’s Degree in Nursing</p></li></ul><h3><strong>What We Offer</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Competitive remuneration package</p></li><li><p>Health insurance coverage</p></li><li><p>Paid annual leave</p></li><li><p>Opportunities for professional development and career growth</p></li></ul><p>If you are passionate about patient care, detail-oriented, and committed to delivering quality healthcare services, we would love to hear from you.</p><p><strong>To apply</strong>, please submit your resume and cover letter.<br /><em>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</em></p>",
